/code></a></li></ol></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/hasOwnProperty\"><code>Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/isPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/setPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.setPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>\n\n<p>Die <strong><code>Math.log2()</code></strong> Funktion gibt den Logarithmus zur Basis<code> 2</code> zurück. Das bedeutet</p>\n\n<p><math display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mo>∀</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mstyle mathvariant=\"monospace\"><mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"thinmathspace\">Math.log2</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mstyle><mo>=</mo><msub><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">log</mo><mn>2</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mtext></mtext><mspace width=\"thickmathspace\"></mspace><mi>y</mi><mspace width=\"thickmathspace\"></mspace><mtext>so das</mtext><mspace width=\"thickmathspace\"></mspace><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"TeX\">\\forall x &gt; 0, \\mathtt{\\operatorname{Math.log2}(x)} = \\log_2(x) = \\text{the unique} \\; y \\; \\text{such that} \\; 2^y = x</annotation></semantics></math></p>\n\n<div id=\"sect2\"><iframe class=\"interactive\" height=\"490\" src=\"https://interactive-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/pages/js/math-log2.html\" title=\"MDN Web Docs Interactive Example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"syntaxbox notranslate\"><code>Math.log2(<var>x</var>)</code></pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"x\"><code>x</code></dt>\n <dd>Eine Zahl.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"rückgabewert","title":"Rückgabewert","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Den Logarithmus zur Basis 2 der gegebenen Zahl. Wenn die Zahl negativ ist, wird <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> zurückgegeben.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"beschreibung","title":"Beschreibung","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Wenn der Wert von <code>x</code> negativ ist, so gibt die Funktion immer <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\" title=\"Die globale NaN Eigenschaft ist ein Wert, der Not-A-Number (keine Zahl) repräsentiert.\"><code>NaN</code></a> zurück.</p>\n\n<p>Weil <code>log2()</code> eine statische Funktion von <code>Math</code> ist, wird es immer als <code>Math.log2()</code> eingesetzt<code>,</code> jedoch nicht als Methode eines erzeugten <code>Math</code> Objektes (<code>Math</code> ist kein Konstruktor).</p>\n\n<p>Diese Funktion ist äquivalent zu Math.log(x) / Math.log(2). Für log2(e) gibt es die Konstante <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/LOG2E\"><code>Math.LOG2E</code></a> welche 1 / <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/LN2\"><code>Math.LN2</code></a> ist.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"beispiele","title":"Beispiele","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"einsatz_von_math.log2()","title":"Einsatz von <code>Math.log2()</code>","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// 1.584962500721156</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// 1</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// 0</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// -Infinity</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>   <span class=\"token comment\">// NaN</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1024</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 10</span>\n</code></pre></div>","titleAsText":"Einsatz von Math.log2()"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"polyfill","title":"Polyfill","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Diese Funktion kann mit folgender Funktion emitiert werden. Es kann sein, dass diese Funktion bei einigen eingabewerten ungenau (ungefähr 1 &lt;&lt; 29) ist. Schachtel die Funktion in <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/round\"><code>Math.round()</code></a> wenn mit Bitmasken gearbeitet wird.</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js line-numbers  language-js notranslate\"><code>Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>log2 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>log2 <span class=\"token operator\">||</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">x</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>x<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token constant\">LOG2E</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"spezifikationen","title":"Spezifikationen","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Spezifikation</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Kommentar</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/#sec-math.log2\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 2015 (6th Edition, ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Math.log2' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>Initiale Definition.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-math.log2\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Math.log2' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Lebender Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität","isH3":false,"query":"javascript.builtins.Math.log2","dataURL":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/log2/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"siehe_auch","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/exp\"><code>Math.exp()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/log\"><code>Math.log()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/log10\"><code>Math.log10()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/log1p\"><code>Math.log1p()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/pow\"><code>Math.pow()</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Beschreibung","id":"beschreibung"},{"text":"Beispiele","id":"beispiele"},{"text":"Polyfill","id":"polyfill"},{"text":"Spezifikationen","id":"spezifikationen"},{"text":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"siehe_auch"}],"summary":"Die Math.log2() Funktion gibt den Logarithmus zur Basis 2 zurück. Das bedeutet","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Math.log2()","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Math.log2()","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Math.log2()","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Math.log2()","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Math.log2()","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Math.log2()","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Math.log2()","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Math.log2()","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"de/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/math/log2","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/de/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/math/log2/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/de/docs/Web","title":"Webtechnologien für Entwickler"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript","title":"JavaScript"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference","title":"JavaScript-Referenz"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects","title":"Globale Objekte"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math","title":"Math"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/log2","title":"Math.log2()"}],"pageTitle":"Math.log2() - JavaScript | MDN","noIndexing":false}}